we have a number of
rows full of content

00:11:18.400 --> 00:11:22.540
that we call, perhaps
unsurprisingly, channels.

00:11:22.540 --> 00:11:25.090
So a row is a channel.

00:11:25.090 --> 00:11:28.540
These channels are the core of
the new home screen experience.

00:11:28.540 --> 00:11:31.090
Each of these channels
is created by a media app

00:11:31.090 --> 00:11:33.970
to display content
relevant to you.

00:11:33.970 --> 00:11:36.490
You might think of each
channel as a window

00:11:36.490 --> 00:11:40.210
into the content
available inside the app.

00:11:40.210 --> 00:11:42.310
Now app surface
content in channels

00:11:42.310 --> 00:11:45.670
by displaying programs, which
are the boxes you see here,

00:11:45.670 --> 00:11:48.130
with TV shows or movies
or video on them.

00:11:48.130 --> 00:11:50.350
So we've got a channel
inside a bunch of boxes.

00:11:50.350 --> 00:11:52.760
Those are called programs.

00:11:52.760 --> 00:11:54.400
These are recommendations
for content

00:11:54.400 --> 00:11:56.620
that's available right
now for you to watch,

00:11:56.620 --> 00:11:58.330
and they could be
on-demand content

00:11:58.330 --> 00:12:00.400
like a movie a TV series.

00:12:00.400 --> 00:12:02.230
Could be a video
clip, live TV show,

00:12:02.230 --> 00:12:05.790
could even be a live
traditional TV channel.

00:12:05.790 --> 00:12:07.260
And actually there's
a couple more.

00:12:07.260 --> 00:12:09.800
Isaac will talk
about that later.

00:12:09.800 --> 00:12:12.850
Now each app gets to decide
what the channel is named,

00:12:12.850 --> 00:12:16.510
what it looks like, what content
appears in it, what metadata

00:12:16.510 --> 00:12:18.760
goes with that content,
and in what order

00:12:18.760 --> 00:12:22.697
the content is displayed
in that channel.

00:12:22.697 --> 00:12:25.030
When you select a program
that seems interesting to you,

00:12:25.030 --> 00:12:27.220
it's going to launch the
app and take you directly

00:12:27.220 --> 00:12:30.550
into the content, starting
playback immediately.

00:12:30.550 --> 00:12:32.989
If you decide to press the
Back button from there,

00:12:32.989 --> 00:12:35.530
the app has the ability to sort
of re-engage you and take you

00:12:35.530 --> 00:12:39.520
to a higher level
screen inside the app.

00:12:39.520 --> 00:12:41.510
Now by structuring the
experience this way,

00:12:41.510 --> 00:12:44.020
what we're allowing apps to
do is surface different types

00:12:44.020 --> 00:12:46.130
of content in the
same experience,

00:12:46.130 --> 00:12:48.610
giving you the choice of
what you're in the mood for.

00:12:48.610 --> 00:12:51.820
Now you could see in the same
experience what's on your DVR,

00:12:51.820 --> 00:12:54.100
what movies are recommended
for you to rent,

00:12:54.100 --> 00:12:55.990
and what on-demand
shows maybe you haven't

00:12:55.990 --> 00:12:57.910
finished binge watching yet.

00:12:57.910 --> 00:12:59.890
In addition, apps
have a lot of control

00:12:59.890 --> 00:13:01.660
about how they want
to present what they

00:13:01.660 --> 00:13:03.430
think is most relevant to you.

00:13:03.430 --> 00:13:05.630
So there's a good balance there.

00:13:05.630 --> 00:13:07.630
All right, actually, let's
go to the play movies

00:13:07.630 --> 00:13:09.860
channel and let's select
