00:13:58.770 --> 00:14:01.020
Now apps have the ability
to provide video previews

00:14:01.020 --> 00:14:03.030
for each program they
put in the channel

00:14:03.030 --> 00:14:05.440
regardless of what type
of content that be.

00:14:05.440 --> 00:14:09.850
That might take the form of a
live preview for live content.

00:14:09.850 --> 00:14:14.050
It might be a trailer for
a movie, for a TV show,

00:14:14.050 --> 00:14:16.650
it could be the series
trailer, or it could be--

00:14:16.650 --> 00:14:18.990
like a season trailer.

00:14:18.990 --> 00:14:21.200
And for video or
digital social content,

00:14:21.200 --> 00:14:23.220
it might be maybe
the first 15 seconds

00:14:23.220 --> 00:14:26.105
of what that content is.

00:14:26.105 --> 00:14:28.230
We think this is going to
drive a lot of engagement

00:14:28.230 --> 00:14:31.110
for our app partners and
we're seeing many developers

00:14:31.110 --> 00:14:32.280
integrating already.

